values:
So i went to see Gordo the other day... i really miss him. we went out on a date to the red lobster where we decided to start with dessert... good way to go. they have awesome key lime pie! (i know were rebels right- don't poke fun)  then we went to see garfield... it was the last movie playing that i could go see without getting home too late (drive from fayetteville to raleigh) it was cute though.  Gordo is moving to utah (if im right - he can correct me if not) to live with bobby, his best friend.  He is going to have to come see me otherwise ill throw a tantrum of all sorts.

When i got back to raleigh i stopped by eddie's house sitting gig... saw some of the old guys including the ex nate, brandon, Eddie (of course ) and good ol' trosky... that was interesting... i would only imagine a guy would give up after you talk to your boyfriend on the phone in that little voice that means your going out or what not.... guess he didn't get the hint... So as i left he proceeded to chase me out. im glad he doesn't live here anymore

The night before i got my wisdom teeth out i went to chapel hill though and i got to meet some of martin's friends... unfortunately since i had to take medicine by a certain time for the wisdom teeth they probably think im all sketch and whatnot... but 50 first dates is a good movie.


Well the past week has been full of.... laughing gas, endocet, percocet, amoxicillian, advil... and many other drugs.  On wednesday i got my wisdom teeth removed. what fun!  i have to say the operation wasn't that bad and i highly recommend it... its better than a day at the beach.   Instead of sleeping until 12 everyday i got to wake up at 8, 12, 4, and so forth taking medication that would put me to sleep for the rest of the day... my kind of vacation! Well after getting dry sockets today (excructiating pain) i got to visit my oral surgeon... but more drugs... so more sleep. so i guess its all good.


Well since i look like complete and utter crap i think ill head off to bed and get some beauty rest before school starts back... that should give me enough time to get a start.... As eddie would say... theres just not enough time for you to get what you need... he'd say something like that


g'night

my overall summer is boring. but i wouldn't really want it to be hectic and full of things.  I rather enjoy my three nights a week at outback. sleeping until 12 and going to lunch with friends... and of course driving to chapel hill to see martin. i can't think of a better way to spend the summer.  In about two weeks i move back to greensboro permanently... (i think)  Getting my house with mary, sonya, and heather... lots of cleaning yay!  but it will be a month to just chill then start the long task of worrying about nursing school... i can't wait!

Now for matt,  not forgetting you i decided to give you half of this entry!! you should be excited....  i have to say i miss our long walks to the caf.. the drunken piggy back rides in the elevator , playing frisbee in the hall and of course pretending to have sex on Brendans bed...   haha... i just thought of the time we tricked him into thinking that i liked you... i know youre not laughing brendan.. but it was a good joke. you were totally convinced.  So, Matt... if things don't work out with Martin you will be the first to know.   Hope to hear from you soon... i miss you... i mean......
what? Anyways... hopefully ill see you this summer Julyish??   

To all a happy summer!! - just remember its one of your last (on a happy note)

Work tonight yay! Last night i went to see harry potter (im like 5 now) it was good though couldn't ask for a better date anyways.        No time to chat... maybe ill actually update this thing one of these days

so..... i went back to outback today. for work.. its the first time in about a month since i quit the greensboro outback... i actually don't know if im allowed to work after quitting... but the raleigh outback is sooo more my style... laid back.  Anyways... money kinda sucked for a saturday night.. but its way better than the greensboro crowd right?...   youre smiling if you know what im talking about.  so anyways. i got to close! yay!!  its weird to be working again... but if you get the chance come see me and you can give me crap. as long as you tip me in one way or another (jk) -ill take the money

i cant wait for monday... i get to see martin

so... it only took me like 7 months but i did it!! you can now know what i look like... and im laughing at you by the way!

Tonight i went to Kanki (japanese steakhouse) with my momma... some good quality mother daughter time... yum yummm! its really good, you outta try it

Martin got his wisdom teeth taken from him today... i feel bad.. i wish i could be there for him.. but i feel his pain... i have to get mine removed soon... i think all the dentists are planning one big vacation... hes the third person i know to get them removed in the past week (Eddie, Nate, Martin)... although eddie doesn't count because hes not human (correction: its not human)  so, if you see a bunch of dentists in hawaii or the bahamas.. youll know why. those bastards gangin up on college students when they come home!

So my hair is no longer red!! yay... back to its original color... i think it looks good, but who cares what i think right.... my biggest hipocrit (sp?) is heather... shes a fashion diva... i think she'd even know if she turned blind... weird senses that girl has....     but i got it cut, and the closest thing to describe it would be the "rachel Hair" ... if you understand that... its not what i asked for. but it works for me.

So, outback this weekend and tuesday... ya know you want to drop by!!   7500 creedmoor rd!!! you can come make fun of me if ya feel like it.


chao, 
al

i did manual labor today! take that martin. (by the way how was your date?)

http://strangeplaces.net/weirdthings/subtitles.html       that will give you a laugh... maybe youll just think im weird.. but whatever


its raining so its time for a nice run.

i think every day i have been back im always running errands....  ive racked up about a 1000 miles in the past week... im always in the car

well its time to run more errands... yay!

went to the lake this weekend... i layed out (without the help of awe-some-rays.. aka.  Kan-sir cough-ins)  so now im tanner than you and probably heather... take that!!!  

ive decided that i use dots too much............................. i don't know what to do............. i think im dot happy............... ill work on it.......... let me know if it annoys you................... i think i picked it up from someone.......... i forgot who......................................


Anyways............haha.... i can't stop

so i saw duplex tonight... pretty funny definitely worth renting.


g'night all... its late



janice: i can read everything in your eyes.. so don't try and hide it
its just indescribable........ thats all i have to say.  he gives me butterflies in my stomach

... off to raleigh... gonna miss this old dorm in some weird way

but ill miss martin more

yay... im 19... now just 2 more years.... haha.  so i had a pretty good birthday... got to take an antomy test (hopefully did good) i could use a 100. that would be nice

so i don't think i have enough cake... anyone wanna get me some more... i only have three to eat in the next couple of days... if you want cake let me know ( i think heather is trying to get me fat: " hey if i can't be skinny please god let my friends be fat"- a good heather quote

19, and bored.......

by the way martin i still have your hat... im holding it for ransom.  100,000 dollars... or something like that

charlotte is terrorizing my cat... hhaha. shes evil

When things in your life seem almost too much to handle, when 24 hours 
in a day are not enough, remember the mayonnaise jar........and the 
beer.

A professor stood before his philosophy class and had some items in 
front of him. When the class began, wordlessly, he picked up a very 
large and empty mayonnaise jar and proceeded to fill it with golf 
balls.  He then asked the students if the jar was full. They agreed 
that it was. 



So the professor then picked up a box of pebbles and poured them into 
the jar. He shook the jar lightly. The pebbles rolled into the open 
areas between golf balls. He then asked the students again if the jar 
was full.  They agreed it was.



The professor next picked up a box of sand and poured it into the jar.  
Of course, the sand filled up everything else. He asked once more if 
the jar was full. The students responded with a unanimous "yes."



The professor then produced two cans of beer from under the table and 
poured the entire contents into the jar, effectively filling the empty 
space between the sand. The students laughed.  "Now," said the 
professor, as the laughter subsided, "I want you to recognize that this 
jar represents your life. The golf balls are the important things--your 
family, your children, your health, your friends, your favorite 
passions--things that if everything else was lost and only they 
remained, your life would still be full. "The pebbles are the other 
things that matter like your job, your house, your car. The sand is 
everything else--the small stuff. 



"If you put the sand into the jar first," he continued, "there is no 
room for the pebbles or the golf balls. The same goes for life. If you 
spend all your time and energy on! the small stuff, you will never have 
room for the things that are important to you. Pay attention to the 
things that are critical to your happiness. Play with your children. 
Take time to get medical checkups. Take your partner out to dinner. 
Play another 18.  There will always be time to clean the house, and fix 
the disposal.

"Take care of the golf balls first, the things that really matter. Set 
your priorities. The rest is just sand."



One of the students raised her hand and inquired what the beer 
represented.  The professor smiled. "I'm glad you asked. It just goes 
to show you that no matter how full your life may seem, there's always 
room for a couple of beers."



~Author Unknown~

The good news is that next week i have absolutely nothing because of the extra few hours i have had lately.  So hopefully i can do good on both of my tests and make for a better weekend.
